    <main class="wide" role="main">
     <div class="bg-gray section" id="content">
      <div class="row">
       <div class="layout">
        <div class="text">
         <h2>
          We’re creating a welcoming and safe community
         </h2>
         <p>
          Indiana University does not tolerate acts of discrimination, hate, harassment, retaliation, or any other act that is damaging to our safe, civil, and inclusive community—and neither should you.
         </p>
         <p>
          If you experience or witness an incident on an IU campus, report it. Your report helps the university take action and prevent future incidents.
         </p>
         <a class="button" href="report/index.html">
          Report an incident
         </a>
        </div>
       </div>
       <!-- /.layout -->
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="bg-crimson bg-dark section" id="">
      <div class="row">
       <div class="layout">
        <h3 class="section-title">
         Call 911 if you need immediate help
        </h3>
        <div class="text">
         <p>
          You must call 911 or
          <a href="resources/index.html">
           contact campus police
          </a>
          if you or someone else is in immediate danger.
         </p>
        </div>
       </div>
       <!-- /.layout -->
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="collapsed bg-none section" id="">
      <div class="row">
       <div class="layout">
        <h2 class="section-title">
         One place to report
        </h2>
        <div class="text">
         <p>
          This website is a resource for anyone at IU who needs to report a student on student incident or wants to better understand issues like harassment, discrimination and learn about university student processes.
         </p>
         <p>
          While IU values open expression and respectful debate, it does not tolerate acts of prejudiced expression that denies a
          <a href="http://studentcode.iu.edu/rights/index.html" title="Students rights code of conduct">
           student the right to freedom from harassment and discrimination
          </a>
          . In response, the university has implemented a university-wide incident reporting system and response protocols for action and assistance.
         </p>
        </div>
       </div>
       <!-- /.layout -->
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="bg-none section" id="">
      <div class="row">
       <div class="layout">
        <div class=" grid thirds">
         <div class="grid-item">
          <div class="panel--interactive">
           <a href="report/index.html">
            <h3 class="title">
             How to report an incident
            </h3>
            <p>
             Submitting an incident report is simple and can be anonymous.
            </p>
           </a>
          </div>
         </div>
         <div class="grid-item">
          <div class="panel--interactive">
           <a href="process/index.html">
            <h3 class="title">
             Incident reporting and response process
            </h3>
            <p>
             Learn about each step in the IU incident reporting and response process.
            </p>
           </a>
          </div>
         </div>
         <div class="grid-item">
          <div class="panel--interactive">
           <a href="http://stopsexualviolence.iu.edu/report/index.html">
            <h3 class="title">
             Report sexual misconduct
            </h3>
            <p>
             To report any form of sexual misconduct, go to the Stop Sexual Violence website.
            </p>
           </a>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
